comments.bodyText:
Component approach can be done by making a component that takes a children as a function or a render prop that gives back data. i.e.
const Auth = ({ children }) => {
  return children(loginInfo) // get loginInfo from somewhere (componentDidMount?)
}

// or with render prop

const Auth = ({ render }) => {
  return render(loginInfo)
}
usage:
<Auth>
{loginInfo => {
  ... add logic here or render component
}}
</Auth>

// or

<Auth render={{loginInfo => { ... }}} />
HOC is just a function that wraps other component, gives it extra prop, and returns it
function withAuth(WrapperComponent) {
  return class WithAuth extends Component {
    render() {
      return <WrapperComponent {...this.props} loginInfo={this.loginInfo} />
    }
  }
}
HOC usage:
const ReviewCard = ({ loginInfo }) => <div>{loginInfo.something}</div>

export default withAuth(ReviewCard)
https://reactjs.org/docs/render-props.html
https://reactjs.org/docs/higher-order-components.html

